  "slug": "pane-di-casa",
  "title": "Pane di casa",
  "subtitle": "Simple Italian house bread with a crisp crust",
  "excerpt": "A plain Italian white loaf with a thin, crackly crust and an even, soft crumb. Straight dough, no pre-ferment, baked hot. Everyday bread for the table.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Pane di casa (house bread) describes the everyday loaf baked in Italian homes across regions. The recipe varies by region (Puglia, Tuscany, Lazio each have their own proportions) but the principle is the same: a simple yeasted white dough baked at high heat. This version follows central Italian proportions documented in Carol Field's The Italian Baker (1985), the foundational English-language source on Italian bread.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pane di casa is the everyday Italian house loaf: a plain white yeasted dough baked hot for a thin, crackly crust and a soft, even crumb. There is no pre-ferment; the flavour comes from a properly proofed dough and a very hot oven. Score the loaf generously before baking, one deep cut along the length or two diagonal slashes. An unscored loaf will burst at a weak point and bake lopsided."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "type": "tip"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Score the loaf generously before it goes in: one deep cut along the length, or two diagonal slashes. An unscored loaf will burst at a weak point and bake lopsided. A lame or a sharp serrated knife both work."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Dough"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "strong-bread-flour",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 500,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "yeast-fast-action",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 7,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "fine-sea-salt",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 10,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "olive-oil",
                  "unit": "tbsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 2,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "whole-milk",
                  "unit": "ml",
                  "prepNote": "lukewarm",
                  "quantity": 320,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mix, autolyse, and knead"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Combine the {{strong-bread-flour}} and {{whole-milk}} in a large bowl. Mix until no dry flour remains, then cover and rest for 20 minutes. This "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "autolyse",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termId": "cmp87mgal0001dcv47448winm"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " lets the gluten develop with minimal effort."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{olive-oil}}. Knead by hand for 8 to 10 minutes until the dough is smooth, elastic, and passes the windowpane test: a small piece should stretch thin enough to see light through without tearing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bulk ferment and shape, 1 hour 30 minutes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shape the dough into a ball and place in a lightly oiled bowl. Cover and leave to bulk ferment at room temperature for 1 hour until doubled."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Turn out onto a lightly floured surface. Knock back gently, then shape into an oval (batard): fold the sides to the centre, roll toward you to create surface tension, and seal the seam."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place seam-side down on a lined baking tray. Cover loosely and prove for 30 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Score and bake, 28 to 32 minutes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 220°C fan with a heavy baking tray inside and a roasting tin on the shelf below."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Score the top of the loaf with one deep cut along its length."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Slide the tray into the oven and throw four ice cubes into the lower tin. Close the door."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bake for 28 to 32 minutes until the crust is golden-brown and the loaf sounds hollow when tapped on the base."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cool on a rack for at least 30 minutes before cutting."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "glossaryTerms": [],
  "recipe": {
    "servings": null,
    "yieldDescription": "1 loaf (about 800 g baked weight)",
